The build fails because the `%prep` section attempts `cd oterm_0.13.0`, but PyPI archives extract to a top-level directory named `oterm-0.13.0` (using a dash instead of an underscore). Fix this by adding `-n oterm-0.13.0` to the `%autosetup` command or correcting the explicit `cd` path in the spec file. Once extraction succeeds, add the necessary Python build dependencies:
BuildRequires: %{python_module pip}
BuildRequires: %{python_module setuptools}